# Playwright Test Standards

Read `QA-PERSONA.md`, `300-page-object-model.mdc`, and `600-guard-rules.mdc`.

## File Header

One `id_scheme` per spec file — header uses **one** scenario ID from that scheme only:

```typescript
// spec: specs/amazon-in/<plan>.md
// scenario: <ID>   ← single ID; must match parent spec id_scheme
```

| Parent spec `id_scheme` | `// scenario:` example |
|-------------------------|-------------------------|
| `feature` | `SRCH-REG-001` |
| `document` | `TC-001` |
| `flow` | `JUICER-003` |

Never combine schemes in one header line. See `200-test-plans.mdc`.

## Imports (required)

**Guest suites:**

```typescript
import { test, expect } from '../../../fixtures/amazon.fixture';
import { testData } from '../../../config/test-data';
```

**Authenticated suites:**

```typescript
import { test, expect, AUTH_STATE_PATH, hasAuthState } from '../../../fixtures/auth.fixture';
import { testData } from '../../../config/test-data';
```

Never import `test` from `@playwright/test` directly. `expect` comes from the same fixture file as `test`.

## Structure

- One manual scenario = one automated test
- Tags in title: `@regression @positive`
- Step comments mirror manual test steps
- **Specs orchestrate** — call page object methods, then assert
- **No locators in specs** — use page object properties/methods

## Assertions (in specs only)

```typescript
await expect(searchResultsPage.firstResult()).toBeVisible();
await expect(productPage.title).not.toBeEmpty();
await expect(cartPage.emptyCartMessage).toBeVisible();
```

## Anti-Patterns (blocked by guard rules)

```typescript
// ❌ Locator in spec
await page.getByPlaceholder('Search Amazon.in').fill('books');

// ❌ Hardcoded URL
await page.goto('https://www.amazon.in');

// ❌ Hardcoded test data
await homePage.search('books');

// ✅ Correct
await homePage.open();
await homePage.search(testData.search.valid);
```

## Reliability

- No `page.waitForTimeout()` without documented reason
- No `networkidle`
- `test.fixme()` only for confirmed app defects with comment
- Use `test.skip()` when env prerequisites missing (e.g. no credentials)
